The bug is the test assumes `setTimeout(..., 100)` resumes **exactly** 100 ms later:

```ts
expect(Date.now() - start).toBe(100);
```

That is not guaranteed. Timers are not precise; `setTimeout` means “run after *at least roughly* this delay when the event loop gets a chance.” The elapsed time may be `100`, `101`, `105`, etc. In a busy CI environment it could be much higher. `Date.now()` is also wall-clock time and has millisecond granularity.

